==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inevitable
<hw>In*ev"i*ta*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inevitabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>in⟦eacute⟧vitable</ets>. See
<er>In-</er> not, and <er>Evitable</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not evitable; incapable of being shunned;
unavoidable; certain.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>inevitable</xex>
hour.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It was <qex>inevitable</qex>; it was necessary; it was planted in
the nature of things.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Irresistible.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Inevitable</xex>
charms.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inevitableness</ent>⟦br⟧
